---
layout: vertical.njk
title: FAQ
pageTitle: Frequently asked questions
pageSubtitle: Common questions about BX-AI+ — search or browse by topic.
permalink: /pages/faq/index.html
breadcrumbs:
  - { label: "BX-AI+", href: "/" }
  - { label: "Pages" }
  - { label: "FAQ" }
---

<div class="row g-3 mb-3">
  <div class="col-12 col-md-7">
    <div class="bx-ai-page__search">
      <i data-lucide="search"></i>
      <input type="search" placeholder="Search the knowledge base…">
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="col-12 col-md-5 d-flex justify-content-md-end gap-2">
    <button class="btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm bx-ai-ask-btn d-inline-flex align-items-center gap-1"
            data-bx-ai-ask
            data-ai-context="faq"
            data-ai-prompt="Help me find the right FAQ topic. I'm looking for…">
      <i data-lucide="sparkles" style="width:13px;height:13px;"></i> Ask BX-AI
    </button>
    <a class="btn btn-primary btn-sm" href="#"><i data-lucide="life-buoy" style="width:13px;height:13px;"></i> Contact support</a>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="row g-3">
  {% for cat in [
    { label: "Getting started",  icon: "rocket",      qs: [
      ["What is BX-AI+?", "BX-AI+ is an AI-centric admin and observability dashboard for the BoxLang runtime. It combines real-time fleet metrics with a contextual AI assistant."],
      ["How do I create a workspace?", "Sign up at /auth/sign-up, pick a subdomain, and you'll be in within seconds."],
      ["Can I import existing agents?", "Yes — bring your own model + prompt definitions via the Import button on AI → Agents."]
    ]},
    { label: "AI & models",      icon: "brain",       qs: [
      ["Which models are supported?", "All Anthropic Claude models (Haiku, Sonnet, Opus). Ollama and self-hosted models on Business and above."],
      ["How does BX-AI guardrail outputs?", "A dedicated guardrails agent runs on every output by default. Configure under Settings → AI defaults."],
      ["Where do prompts live?", "AI → Prompt library. Star your favorites, share with the team, version them."]
    ]},
    { label: "Billing",          icon: "dollar-sign", qs: [
      ["How is usage measured?", "By tokens (prompt + completion). Each plan includes a daily cap; overages are billed at $0.40 per 1k tokens."],
      ["Do you offer annual discounts?", "Yes — 20% off when you pay yearly."],
      ["Can I cancel anytime?", "Yes — your workspace remains active until the end of the current period."]
    ]},
    { label: "Security",         icon: "shield-check", qs: [
      ["Is data used to train models?", "No. Your data is never used to train or fine-tune any underlying model."],
      ["Is BX-AI+ SOC2 certified?", "Type I attestation in place. Type II is in progress — see status.bx-ai.io."],
      ["How do I enable SSO?", "Available on Business and above via Settings → Security → SSO."]
    ]}
  ] %}
  <div class="col-12 col-xl-6">
    <div class="bx-widget" style="height:100%;">
      <div class="bx-widget__head">
        <div class="bx-widget__title-wrap" style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:0.6rem;">
          <span class="bx-stat-card__icon" aria-hidden="true"><i data-lucide="{{ cat.icon }}"></i></span>
          <h3 class="bx-widget__title" style="margin:0;">{{ cat.label }}</h3>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="bx-widget__body">
        <div class="accordion" id="acc-{{ loop.index }}">
          {% for q in cat.qs %}
          <div class="accordion-item">
            <h2 class="accordion-header">
              <button class="accordion-button {% if not loop.first %}collapsed{% endif %}" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#acc-{{ loop.index0 }}-{{ loop.index }}">
                {{ q[0] }}
              </button>
            </h2>
            <div id="acc-{{ loop.index0 }}-{{ loop.index }}" class="accordion-collapse collapse {% if loop.first %}show{% endif %}" data-bs-parent="#acc-{{ loop.index0 }}">
              <div class="accordion-body">{{ q[1] }}</div>
            </div>
          </div>
          {% endfor %}
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  {% endfor %}
</div>
